programme.title: Final Destination
programme.desc: Alex is about to board a plane on a school trip. He gets a premonition that the plane will explode. It does, and the FBI suspects that Alex could be responsible for the explosion.

programme.title: Bruce Almighty
programme.desc: Bruce Nolan is a frustrated TV reporter stuck doing puff pieces while his colleague gets the anchor job he covets. Bruce blames God for all the bad things happening to him and demands an explanation from Him. Bruce meets God and tells Him that he can run the world in a better way. God gives him a chance to run the world and Himself goes on a vacation. Bruce, endowed with all the powers of God, decides to put his life on track. Slowly, Bruce realises that he can't run the world and only God can.

programme.title: The Incredibles
programme.desc: Winning the 77th Academy award for the Best Animated feature, the film directed by Brad Bird, revolves around a family of superheroes who are forced to hide their superpowers and lead mundane lives due to several lawsuits filed against them. Although, Mr. Incredible's desire to help people drags the whole family into a battle with the evil Syndrome who has been responsible for murdering countless retired superheroes.

programme.title: Shanghai Knights
programme.desc: Jackie Chan and Owen Wilson reprise their roles as Chon and Roy and head to London to take revenge on the Chinese rebel who killed Chon's father. But during their pursuit, they stumble upon a dangerous conspiracy.

programme.title: Black Panther
programme.desc: T'Challa returns home to the isolated, advanced nation of Wakanda to take his rightful place as king, after the death of his father, and as Black Panther, the protector of the people. But a powerful enemy, with ties to his family's past, threatens to start an all-out war and jeopardize Wakanda and the world.

programme.title: The Maze Runner
programme.desc: Thomas wakes to find himself among young boys in an enclosed setting that turns out to be the centre of a maze. With no memory of his past to guide him, Thomas and his friends plot to escape and reclaim their identities, unaware of the horrors that await them.

programme.title: Jack The Giant Slayer
programme.desc: Jack, a young boy, is in awe of the legend of Erik, an ancient king who won against a strong army of giants. Isabelle, a young princess, is fascinated with the same legend and becomes a love interest of Jack. He unknowingly reignites the same war his beloved hero had ended centuries ago. Once again, the giants are back on Earth to destroy and Jack must prepare himself to fight them. He gears up to save his kingdom, its people and the love of his life, Isabelle. When he emerges victorious, he becomes a hero like the legend of Erik.

programme.title: Maleficent
programme.desc: Maleficent is a kind-hearted fairy, who wants peace to prevail in the kingdom. She is deceived by the love of her life, Stefan, who wants to be the king. In a turn of events, he cuts her wings and is crowned the king. A scorned Maleficent is hell-bent on attaining justice in her own ways. When she realises that Stefan is blessed with a daughter, Aurora, she places a curse on her. She reveals that on her sixteenth birthday, she will prick her finger on the spindle of a spinning wheel, which will cause her to fall into a deathlike sleep. Later, Maleficent realises that Aurora is the only one who can help restore peace in the kingdom and to her too.

programme.title: A Bug's Life
programme.desc: Flik, an odd ball of an ant, may be pint sized but he has tremendous courage. When the anthill he resides in is threatened by arrogant grasshoppers, he sets out to create an army to deal with them, recruiting the most incompetent bugs of course. A man with exceptional humour inducing skills, Dave Foley lends his voice to play Flik. Directors John Lasseter, and Andrew Stanton procure some of the biggest names on television and film for 'A Bug's Life'. Julia Louis-Dreyfuss, Kevin Spacey and Hayden Pannettiere are but a few.

programme.title: Raya and the Last Dragon
programme.desc: Sisu, a dragon, sacrifices herself and transfers all her powers into a gem when a few evil forces attack the kingdom of Kumandra, where humans and dragons peacefully co-exist. Several years later, the kingdom stands divided into separate clans who fight to gain possession of the magical gem which is shattered into pieces and scattered all over. Raya, a warrior's daughter, vows to track down Sisu and reunite the people of the kingdom.

programme.title: Doctor Strange
programme.desc: Stephen Strange, a neurosurgeon, loses the use of his hands after an accident and goes to the Kamar-Taj with the hope of being healed. He is taken in by the Ancient One, a sorcerer, who teaches him the mystic arts, which he must then use to stop the evil Kaecilius.

programme.title: X-Men: Apocalypse
programme.desc: An immensely powerful ancient mutant rises again and wishes to cleanse humankind in order to create a new world order. He recruits some powerful mutants, making them believe that mutants are superior to humans and it is their right to rule. To counter him, Raven tries to pull Charles out of his depressed state and lead a team of X-Men.

programme.title: Out of Paradise
programme.desc: Dorj and Suren live as wanderers in the Mongolian grasslands. Things get complicated as they journey to Ulaanbaatar to seek treatment for Suren's pregnancy complications.

programme.title: Another Love
programme.desc: Julika, a physiotherapist, is a young widow who lives in the past. She meets Konstantin, a city guide, whose carefree ways inspire her to explore a new kind of love.

programme.title: A Minute's Silence
programme.desc: An English teacher returns to her hometown and starts having an affair with one of her students. However, she suddenly dies and the student struggles to pick up the pieces.

programme.title: Zero Bridge
programme.desc: Dilawar, a youngster from Srinagar, indulges in petty thefts so that he can raise money and leave his hometown. But his plans go awry when he develops feelings for a young and bright woman, Bani.

programme.title: Melissa
programme.desc: Melissa, an abused little girl, is abducted and taken to an unknown location. She then develops a strange bond with her captor.

programme.title: Truth And Justice
programme.desc: Hoping to start afresh, Andres and his wife Kroot move to a new house. However, he faces several challenges because of his neighbour and traditional beliefs.

programme.title: Helen
programme.desc: When a student goes missing, the police ask Helen, an orphan, to portray the person in a reenactment of the crime scene, which then allows her to come to terms with her troubled life.

programme.title: Stormbreaker
